race.description: Hawaii Five Oh @ Vinery Stud Handicap (Bm64)
race.comment: SHOW BUSINESS (8) missed by a whisker first-up at Hawkesbury then stepped up in distance and had no trouble accounting for a Class 1 field of mares over 1200m at Kembla last start. Drops 1.5kgs with the claim and has further improvement to come so stick with her. FLEETING SPIRIT (7) has raced well this prep without winning. Tired close to home at Rosehill last time when fresh from a five-week let-up. Should tighten up following that hit out and from a good gate with Clark to ride makes plenty of appeal. TASORAAY (2) led by a clear margin into the lane but was a spent force soon after when resuming over 1300m at Randwick recently. Sure to take a lot from that outing and will be tougher to catch this time. ROMAN FORUM (10) led and gave a great sight over 1200m at Gosford last start. Lightly raced and has plenty of scope for improvement. CHICAMA (5) steps back to midweek company and can improve on a modest sixth at Randwick four weeks ago.
